## PHP OOP Bank System

    A simple PHP project demonstrating Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts such as Interfaces, Traits, Abstract Classes, Inheritance, Polymorphism, Encapsulation, Magic Methods, and Static properties in a banking system simulation.

    This project includes Savings Accounts and Current Accounts, with deposit, withdrawal, and interest calculation functionality.

| Concept              | How It’s Used                                                                          |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Encapsulation**    | Private properties `$balance`, `$ownerName`, `$accountNumber` with getters.            |
| **Inheritance**      | `SavingsAccount` and `CurrentAccount` inherit from `BankAccount`.                      |
| **Polymorphism**     | Overriding `withdraw()` behaves differently for savings vs current accounts.           |
| **Abstract Classes** | `BankAccount` defines common methods and abstract `calculateInterest()`.               |
| **Interfaces**       | `AccountInterface` ensures all accounts implement `deposit`, `withdraw`, `getBalance`. |
| **Traits**           | `LoggerTrait` reused for logging without inheritance.                                  |
| **Magic Methods**    | `__construct`, `__toString`, `__get` for convenient object handling.                   |
| **Static Members**   | Track total accounts with `BankAccount::$totalAccounts`.                               |

## File Structure
        php-bank-system/
    ├── src/
    │   ├── AccountInterface.php
    │   ├── LoggerTrait.php
    │   ├── BankAccount.php
    │   ├── SavingsAccount.php
    │   └── CurrentAccount.php
    ├── index.php
    └── README.md
 